HEADWORD: Dextronic
<hw>Dex*tron"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or derived from, dextrose; <as>as,
<ex>dextronic</ex> acid</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Dextronic acid</b></col>, <cd>a sirupy substance obtained
by the partial oxidation of various carbohydrates, as dextrose,
etc.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dextrorotary</ent>⟦br⟧
